. Inst. Nav. |author=Portney, Joseph |year=1973 |volume=20 |issue=3 |pages=208\u201318 |title=The Polar Flap: Byrd's Flight Confirmed |doi=10.1002/j.2161-4296.1973.tb01173.x}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"fC461\">{{cite journal |journal=J. Inst. Nav. |author=Portney, Joseph |year=1992 |volume=39 |issue=2 |pages=255\u201364 |title=History of Aerial Polar Navigation |doi=10.1002/j.2161-4296.1992.tb01878.x}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"kAWPY\">{{cite book |last1=Pool |first1=Beekman H. |title=Polar Extremes: The World of Lincoln Ellsworth |date=2002 |publisher=University of Alaska Press |location=Fairbanks, Alaska |isbn=1889963437 |page=97}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ucqIu\">{{Cite web|title = Ditching of 'America'|url = http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/America-NX206.htm|website = www.check-six.com|accessdate = December 16, 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"6SieQ\">New York Times. July 7, 1927.</ref>\n<ref name=\"iNgXi\">New York Times. July 20, 1927.</ref>\n<ref name=\"mheH3\">[https://books.google.com/books?id=ICoDAAAAMBAJ&pg=-PA9&dq=1930+plane+%22Popular&hl=en&ei=GTuNTr-hF4abtwfUopWLDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CF0Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q&f=true \"Why We May Wait 20 Years for Ocean Airliners\"] ''Popular Science'', August 1927, p. 9</ref>\n<ref name=\"1GPaH\">U.S. Navy Register, 1930.</ref>\n<ref name=\"zw56a\">The''Admiral Byrd Broadcasts'' ''The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio,'' Oxford University Press, 1998, p.5.</ref>\n<ref name=\"QBmaR\">{{Cite news|title = BYRD IS HONORED BY SANTO DOMINGO; Explorer Gets Medal of the Order of Columbus at Ceremony at Republic's Embassy|url = https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E00E6D8133FE333A05752C1A9649C946493D6CF|newspaper = The New York Times|date = February 11, 1945|access-date = December 16, 2015|issn = 0362-4331|first = Special To The New York|last = Times}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"SrP7R\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|title=A bordo del Monte Olimpo en Alta Mar|newspaper=[[El Mercurio]]|location=[[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]|pages=|lan