85, 59 Stat. 536</ref>\n<ref name=\"pIJsV\">Navy Book of Distinguished Service. pg. 187.</ref>\n<ref name=\"idz6u\">{{Cite web|title = Richard Byrd 1927 File: fl0045957.php|url = http://www.gao.gov/10/fl0045957.php|website = www.gao.gov|accessdate = December 16, 2015}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"BXenH\">U.S. Navy Register of Commissioned Officers. 1919. p. 406.</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{Cite web\n |accessdate  = July 14, 2007\n |url         = http://library.osu.edu/sites/archives/polar/flight/controversy.php\n |title       = The North Pole Flight of Richard E. Byrd: An Overview of the Controversy\n |publisher   = Polar Archival Program, Ohio State University\n |year        = 2007\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20071013144532/http://library.osu.edu/sites/archives/polar/flight/controversy.php\n |archivedate = October 13, 2007\n |df          = mdy-all\n}}\n* {{Cite web\n |url=http://www.dioi.org/vols/wa0.pdf\n  |title=Richard E. Byrd's 1926 Flight Towards the North Pole\n  |date=October 25, 2007}}\n* {{cite book\n |url=https://archive.org/details/topolediarynoteb00byrd\n  |url-access=registration\n  |title=''To the Pole: The Diary and Notebook of Richard E. Byrd'', 1925\u20131927\n  |publisher=Ohio State University Press\n  |date=1998|last1=Byrd\n |first1=Richard Evelyn\n |last2=Goerler\n |first2=Raimund Erhard\n }}\n* {{Cite web\n  |url=http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/America-NX206.htm\n  |title=The Flight of the 'America' \u2013 1927\n  |date=October 25, 2007}}\n* {{Cite web\n  |url=http://www.south-pole.com/p0000107.htm\n  |title=Richard E. Byrd 1888\u20131957\n  |date=October 25, 2007}}\n* {{Cite web\n |url=http://www.navworld.com/navcerebrations/polar_flap.htm\n  |title=A navigation expert's look at how Byrd's claim is one possible interpretation of his diary.\n  |date=October 25, 2007}}\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=iuIDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA225&dq=Popular+Science+1930+plane+%22Popular+Mechanics%22&hl=en&ei=F1pgTsXY